{"tid":1848783,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"連CNN都串鳩柒婆: 上年力推反蒙面法 依家今日佢晒戴口罩出嚟見記者","createTime":"2020-01-28T16:03:39.000Z","updateTime":"2020-01-28T18:55:26.000Z","uid":28114,"like":126,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":28,"replies":[{"pid":"3edd234f5613859570d5ec4ae51c10e0c3b6106a","tid":1848783,"uid":28114,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-28T16:03:39.000Z","msg":"Last year Carrie Lam banned face masks. Now, she's wearing one in a press conference<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://dynaimage.cdn.cnn.com/cnn/digital-images/org/76bc9236-1170-46a9-b8fa-136eeec9a7d0.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdynaimage.cdn.cnn.com%2Fcnn%2Fdigital-images%2Forg%2F76bc9236-1170-46a9-b8fa-136eeec9a7d0.jpg&h=db130ec9&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-01-28-20-intl-hnk/h_de6f7529da8c257da95ca55439097408\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2Fasia%2Flive-news%2Fcoronavirus-outbreak-01-28-20-intl-hnk%2Fh_de6f7529da8c257da95ca55439097408&d=rcEdfnhTqGmqsB%2B6X%2FYCGQomF%2BlBZ%2FxAFwVMru4Rc7Q%3D&h=9daafdb6\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2Fasia%2Flive-news%2Fcoronavirus-outbreak-01-28-20-intl-hnk%2Fh_de6f7529da8c257da95ca55439097408&h=53a3071b\" target=\"_blank\">https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-01-28-20-intl-hnk/h_de6f7529da8c257da95ca55439097408</a>"},{"pid":"b0a525e9ec96f72019918acf13238c8681dc9a8e","tid":1848783,"uid":28114,"like":14,"dislike":0,"score":14,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-28T16:06:07.000Z","msg":"Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam arrived at press conference today wearing a surgical face mask, alongside several other members of her senior team.<br />\n<br />\nJust a few months ago, the sight of government officials wearing masks would have been unthinkable -- for a very different reason.<br />\n<br />\nToday's press conference, and the officials' decision to wear masks, come as the Hong Kong government look to step up efforts to enforce better public health measures.<br />\n<br />\nAs of today, there are eight confirmed cases of the coronavirus in Hong Kong. At the press conference, Lam announced additional measures including restricted travel across the Chinese border.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://dynaimage.cdn.cnn.com/cnn/digital-images/org/71af942d-f7f6-4397-af5e-2eacf347c9e4.jpeg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdynaimage.cdn.cnn.com%2Fcnn%2Fdigital-images%2Forg%2F71af942d-f7f6-4397-af5e-2eacf347c9e4.jpeg&h=cfeb0ac6&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nProtesters in Hong Kong on November 11, 2019. ANTHONY WALLACE/AFP via Getty Images<br />\n<br />\nMasks in a different context: But a little over three months ago, in early October, Lam had invoked colonial-era emergency powers to ban people from wearing face masks in public assemblies as anti-government, pro-democracy protests rocked the city.<br />\n<br />\nProtesters often wore face masks, as well as helmets and goggles, to obscure their identity and protect against tear gas when battling riot police on the streets.<br />\n<br />\nFor the entire second half of 2019, face masks were a symbol of the city's political crisis, and a statement on where you stood. When Lam announced the face mask ban, she said it would help &quot;stop violence and restore calm to society,&quot; and act as a deterrent for protesters."},{"pid":"580db8cd5a164af5fb9b9c41ef8a0ad2c0ed9717","tid":1848783,"uid":14449,"like":12,"dislike":0,"score":12,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-28T16:10:29.000Z","msg":"林鄭: 傾日叫阿強搵100個防暴去掃cnn office"},{"pid":"69f55aaa5e8cdd837efbd7239ff3d89efa17f386","tid":1848783,"uid":108910,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"580db8cd5a164af5fb9b9c41ef8a0ad2c0ed9717","tid":1848783,"uid":14449,"like":12,"dislike":0,"score":12,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-28T16:10:29.000Z","msg":"林鄭: 傾日叫阿強搵100個防暴去掃cnn office"},"citedBy":0,"rep